@nerdlypainter @maximaxoo Americans take American salad ideas - lettuce and a creamy dressing and then add in some of the ingredients you find in horiatiki.  They call this a Greek salad.  An Asian salad has some things you find in Asian food.  A Mediterranean salad has some things you find in the Med...

@maximaxoo @sousibrown Horiatiki if I recall, does not contain lettuce.  It's peppers, cucumbers, tomatoes, olives with feta in a lemon and olive oil dressing.  "Greek salad" is Americanized, adds chopped romaine lettuce and often other things like herbs, radishes, etc.  Oil and vinegar + oregano.

Greek salad also has cucumber in @sainsburys. Furthermore it’s seasoned with oregano and not dill.
